The Group of Seven (G7) industrialized countries  will discuss economic support for South Africa when they hold a summit in  Italy in July, a news report said here Thursday.
The G7, at its summit in Naples July 8-10, is expected to agree to hold a  new multilateral conference to support South Africa, Kyodo News Service cited  official sources as saying.
The G7 members are Britain, Canada, France, Germany, Italy, Japan and the  United States.
